  "body": "The fact that net_processing uses a mix of mockable tand non-mockable time functions made it hard to write functional tests for #19988.\r\n\r\nI'm opening this as a separate PR as I believe it's independently useful. In some ways this doesn't go quite as far as it could, as there are now several data structures that could be converted to `std::chrono` types as well now. I haven't done that here, but I'm happy to reconsider that.",
